OL,3,CWater industry review unlikely to
OL,4,Cspark required change, claims Feargal
OL,5,CSharkey
OL,7,F"I also don't think you can talk about
OL,8,Fabolishing Ofwat without considering
OL,9,Fthe future of the Environment Agency `
OL,10,Fand taking a long, hard look at the
OL,11,FEnvironment Department (Defra), as
OL,12,Fwell as the lack of action from
OL,13,Fgovernment ministers for many years.
OL,14,FThey are just as culpable."
OL,16,FSharkey said governments have had the
OL,17,Fpower to punish water companies over
OL,18,Fsewage pollution, or the "scandal" of
OL,19,Fpaying huge bonuses to bosses, but had
OL,20,Fchosen not to use them for years.
